Name: NPH_Norn
English: Elesh Norn, Grand Cenobite. Legendary Creature — Phyrexian Praetor. Vigilance. Other creatures you control get +2/+2. Creatures your opponents control get -2/-2. “The Gitaxians whisper among themselves of other worlds. If they exist, we must bring Phyrexia’s magnificence to them.”
Notes: There's a difference between the MTGA and judge promo of this card. The judge promo version is believed to be the correct one.

Name: NPH_Ura
English: Urabrask the Hidden. Legendary Creature — Phyrexian Praetor. Creatures you control have haste. Creatures your opponents control enter the battlefield tapped. When the Mirran resistance arrived, the furnace dwellers looked to Urabrask for guidance. His decree stunned the others: “Let them be.”

Name: NPH_Jin
English: Jin-Gitaxias, Core Augur. Legendary Creature — Phyrexian Praetor. Flash. At the beginning of your end step, draw seven cards. Each opponent’s maximum hand size is reduced by seven. “It is not a goal, but a process—the process of creating the perfect Phyrexia.”

Name: NPH_Sheo
English: Sheoldred, Whispering One. Legendary Creature — Phyrexian Praetor. Swampwalk. At the beginning of your upkeep, return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield. At the beginning of each opponent’s upkeep, that player sacrifices a creature.

Name: NPH_Vorin
English: Vorinclex, Voice of Hunger. Legendary Creature — Phyrexian Praetor. Trample. Whenever you tap a land for mana, add one mana of any type that land produced. Whenever an opponent taps a land for mana, that land doesn’t untap during its controller’s next untap step.

Name: KHM_Vorin
English: Vorinclex, Monstrous Raider. Legendary Creature — Phyrexian Praetor. Trample, haste. If you would put one or more counters on a permanent or player, put twice that many of each of those kinds of counters on that permanent or player instead. If an opponent would put one or more counters on a permanent or player, they put half that many of each of those kinds of counters on that permanent or player instead, rounded down.

Name: NEO_Jin
English: Jin-Gitaxias, Progress Tyrant. Legendary Creature — Phyrexian Praetor. Whenever you cast an artifact, instant, or sorcery spell, copy that spell. You may choose new targets for the copy. This ability triggers only once each turn. Whenever an opponent casts an artifact, instant, or sorcery spell, counter that spell. This ability triggers only once each turn.
Notes: Meanings for ability and trigger clash with ONE_Norn

Name: NEO_Tami
English: Tamiyo, Compleated Sage. Legendary Planeswalker — Tamiyo. Compleated. Tap up to one target artifact or creature. It doesn’t untap during its controller’s next untap step. Exile target nonland permanent card with mana value X from your graveyard. Create a token that’s a copy of that card. Create Tamiyo’s Notebook, a legendary colorless artifact token with “Spells you cast cost 2 less to cast” and “Draw a card.”

Name: Yawg_Test
English: Yawgmoth's Testament. Sorcery. Until end of turn, you may play face-up cards you own from exile. If a card would be put into your graveyard or exile from anywhere this turn, put it on the bottom of your library instead.
Notes: We're using the corrected version WotC published.

Name: DOM_Scriptures
English: From void evolved Phyrexia. Great Yawgmoth, Father of Machines, saw its perfection. Thus the Grand Evolution began.
Notes: A couple glyphs are wrong in this art piece. See the artist's blueprint for the correct version. The translation shows up on Dark Ritual from Urza's Saga.

Name: UMA_Altar
English: Unskin.
Notes: Deduced from the card's flavor text.

Name: SLD_Swamp
English: Swamp. Basic Land — Swamp.

Name: MBS_Trailer
English: We are perfection made flesh. Our voice calls out to the lost and the broken. They fear death, even as we offer immortality. We will flay the false skin of this world, to reveal the face of a New Phyrexia. The great work has begun.
Notes: Resolution is very low quality and confidence on the correctness of every glyph is shaky.

Name: NPH_Trailer
English: The great work of New Phyrexia is complete. New sources of mana power the Machine Orthodoxy. Beneath phyrexian skin, the heart of mirrodin burns. The body is whole, but whispers splinter the mind. The father of machines is coming. Destroyer.
Notes: Resolution is very low quality and confidence on the correctness of every glyph is shaky.

Name: SLD_Praetors
English: Phyrexian Praetors. Compleat Edition. Phyrexian Praetors. Compleat Edition. Foil Edition

Name: MTGSalvation
English: Phyrexian Language.

Name: SNC_Ura
English: Urabrask, Heretic Praetor. Legendary Creature — Phyrexian Praetor. Haste. At the beginning of your upkeep, exile the top card of your library. You may play it this turn. At the beginning of each opponent’s upkeep, the next time they would draw a card this turn, instead they exile the top card of their library. They may play it this turn.

Name: DMU_Sheo
English: Sheoldred, the Apocalypse. Legendary Creature — Phyrexian Praetor. Deathtouch. Whenever you draw a card, you gain 2 life. Whenever an opponent draws a card, they lose 2 life.

Name: DMU_Ajani
English: Ajani, Sleeper Agent. Legendary Planeswalker — Ajani. Compleated. Reveal the top card of your library. If it’s a creature or planeswalker card, put it into your hand. Otherwise, you may put it on the bottom of your library. Distribute three +1/+1 counters among up to three target creatures. They gain vigilance until end of turn. You get an emblem with “Whenever you cast a creature or planeswalker spell, target opponent gets two poison counters.”

Name: NPH_Dismember
English: Dismember. Instant. Target creature gets -5/-5 until end of turn.

Name: MBS_PsyCrawl
English: Psychosis Crawler. Artifact Creature — Phyrexian Horror. Psychosis Crawler’s power and toughness are each equal to the number of cards in your hand. Whenever you draw a card, each opponent loses 1 life.

Name: ONE_Norn
English: Elesh Norn, Mother of Machines. Legendary Creature — Phyrexian Praetor. Vigilance. If a permanent entering the battlefield causes a triggered ability of a permanent you control to trigger, that ability triggers an additional time. Permanents entering the battlefield don’t cause abilities of permanents your opponents control to trigger.
Notes: Meanings for ability and trigger clash with NEO_Jin

Name: ONE_Plains
English: Plains. Basic Land — Plains.

Name: ONE_Island
English: Island. Basic Land — Island.

Name: ONE_Swamp
English: Swamp. Basic Land — Swamp.

Name: ONE_Mountain
English: Mountain. Basic Land — Mountain.

Name: ONE_Forest
English: Forest. Basic Land — Forest.

Name: ONE_Article
English: Greatness, at any cost. Fall to your knees and welcome our embrace. Mother of Machines. All will be one. A mixed organic and non-organic sentient being, or a fully non-organic sentient being. A fully organic sentient being.

Name: BeadleGrimms
English: From Beadle & Grimm's: Behold New Phyrexia! Surrender to perfection on February 18, 2023. Subscribe and welcome our embrace.

Name: ONE_Live
English: We are Phyrexia. We will sow perfection into the soft flesh of this world.

Name: BRO_BoneSaw
English: We will cleanse their impurities.

Name: NPH_Agent
English: Blighted Agent. Creature — Phyrexian Human Rogue. Infect. Blighted Agent can’t be blocked. “Urabrask may suspect our surveillance, but he cannot stop it.” — Avaricta, Gitaxian sective.

Name: NPH_Elf
English: Glistener Elf. Creature — Phyrexian Elf Warrior. Infect.

Name: NPH_Batterskull
English: Batterskull. Artifact — Equipment. Living weapon. Equipped creature gets +4/+4 and has vigilance and lifelink. Return Batterskull to its owner’s hand. Equip.

Name: NPH_InkNexus
English: Inkmoth Nexus. Land. Add. Inkmoth Nexus becomes a 1/1 Phyrexian Blinkmoth artifact creature with flying and infect until end of turn. It’s still a land.

Name: C19_Krrik
English: K'rrik, Son of Yawgmoth. Legendary Creature — Phyrexian Horror Minion. Lifelink. For each B in a cost, you may pay 2 life rather than pay that mana. Whenever you cast a black spell, put a +1/+1 counter on K'rrik, Son of Yawgmoth.

Name: ONE_Arena
English: Phyrexian Arena. Enchantment. At the beginning of your upkeep, you draw a card and you lose 1 life.

Name: NPH_Annex
English: Norn's Annex. Artifact. Creatures can’t attack you or planeswalkers you control unless their controller pays W/P for each of those creatures.

Name: ONE_Jace
English: Jace, the Perfected Mind. Legendary Planeswalker — Jace. Compleated. Until your next turn, up to one target creature gets -3/-0. Target player mills three cards. Then if a graveyard has twenty or more cards in it, you draw three cards. Otherwise, you draw a card. Target player mills three times X cards.

Name: ONE_Vraska
English: Vraska, Betrayal's Sting. Legendary Planeswalker — Vraska. Compleated. You draw a card and you lose 1 life. Proliferate. Target creature becomes a Treasure artifact with “Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color” and loses all other card types and abilities. If target player has fewer than nine poison counters, they get a number of poison counters equal to the difference.

Name: ONE_Lukka
English: Lukka, Bound to Ruin. Legendary Planeswalker — Lukka. Compleated. Add R/G. Spend this mana only to cast creature spells or activate abilities of creatures. Create a 3/3 green Phyrexian Beast creature token with toxic 1. Lukka deals X damage divided as you choose among any number of target creatures and/or planeswalkers, where X is the greatest power among creatures you controlled as you activated this ability.

Name: ONE_Nissa
English: Nissa, Ascended Animist. Legendary Planeswalker — Nissa. Compleated. Create an X/X green Phyrexian Horror creature token, where X is Nissa, Ascended Animist’s loyalty. Destroy target artifact or enchantment. Until end of turn, creatures you control get +1/+1 for each Forest you control and gain trample.
Notes: Enchantment is written here with the word for arena.

Name: ONE_Nahiri
English: Nahiri, the Unforgiving. Legendary Planeswalker — Nahiri. Compleated. Until your next turn, up to one target creature attacks a player each combat if able. Discard a card, then draw a card. Exile target creature or Equipment card with mana value less than Nahiri’s loyalty from your graveyard. Create a token that’s a copy of it. That token gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step.
Notes: An instance of equipment here is just written in english.

Name: ONE_Trailer
Notes: English voiceover does not directly translate to written text on screen.

Name: Keyboard
Notes: Bad resolution makes it hard to get some of the glyphs right.

Name: NPH_Misstep
English: Mental Misstep. Instant. Counter target spell with mana value 1.
